<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-209-079 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 649 912</DOCID><JOURNAL>CVGIP: Image Understanding  March 1991 v53 n2 p219(8).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Note: Reconstructing a 3-D depth map from one or more images.andO;(technical)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Shao, Min; Chellappa, Rama; Simchony, Tal.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Several algorithms are presented for generating accurate,unambiguous and dense surface depth and orientation maps of asurface from its image intensities.andP;  They combine the advantagesof shape-from-shading (SFS) and stereo vision methods.andP;  An SFSalgorithm is presented that couples the generation of depth andorientation maps and ensures consistency in the reconstructedsurface depth and its orientation.andP;  The single image SFS algorithmis then extended to utilize stereo images.andP;  An alternate approachis also presented for combining stereo and SFS techniques.andP;  Analgorithm is presented for combining sparse depth measurementswith an orientation map to reconstruct a surface.andP;  This algorithmcan be combined with the other algorithms to solve SFS problemswith sparse depth measurements.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Image ProcessingThree-Dimensional GraphicsMapsStereo VisionShapeShadingAlgorithmsComputer VisionTheoretical ResearchNew Technique.andO;Feature:   illustrationchart.andO;Caption:   Camera set-up for stereo images. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>